          "author_association": "MEMBER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #28\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#321\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cv2_processing/crop.py:90`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cv2_processing/crop.py:93`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cupy_processing/crop.py:87`\n- `pd_book_tools/image_processing/cupy_processing/crop.py:90`\n\nNegative edge values pass the dimension check and feed Python slicing.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Slice wraparound can return surprising crops or empty arrays.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Validate all crop edge arguments are non-negative integers.\n- Add CPU and GPU tests.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
